name: Accessibility Model
description:
The economic and man-made resources that sustain human well-being are not distributed
evenly across the world, but are instead heavily concentrated in cities.
Poor access to opportunities and services offered by urban centers
(a function of distance, transport infrastructure, and the spatial distribution of cities)
is a major barrier to improved livelihoods and overall development.
The model calculates travel time to cities via surface transport (air travel is not considered).
The model output is used as input to the economic model and to inform the design
and implementation of development policies. The accessibility model is also used to estimate travel
time to markets, which is used to dis-aggregate market prices to a pixel level.

parameters.name: destination
parameters.description: Destination we are calculating travel time to

parameters.name: trunk_road_speed_offset
parameters.description: The most important roads in a country's system that aren't motorways.

parameters.name: primary_road_speed_offset
parameters.description: The next most important roads in a country's system after trunk roads. They often link larger towns.

parameters.name: secondary_road_speed_offset
parameters.description: The next most important roads in a country's system after primary roads. They often link towns.

parameters.name: tertiary_road_speed_offset
parameters.description: The next most important roads in a country's system after secondary roads. They often link smaller towns and villages.

parameters.name: unclassified_road_speed_offset
parameters.description: The least important through roads in a country's system. They often link villages and hamlets.

outputs.name: travel time
outputs.description: travel time to the nearest destination in minutes.
outputs.unit_description: minutes required to travel to the nearest destination
